findings.recommendation:
In function 'ownerWithdrawAll' at line 30: replace tx.origin with msg.sender:
  // WRONG
  require(tx.origin == owner, "Not owner");

  // CORRECT
  require(msg.sender == owner, "Not owner");

msg.sender is the immediate caller and correctly blocks malicious intermediary contracts. tx.origin reflects only the original EOA and is bypassable via phishing.

Add an explicit balance check before the transfer:
  require(balances[msg.sender] >= amount, 'Insufficient balance');
  balances[msg.sender] -= amount;   // Update state first
  payable(msg.sender).transfer(amount);

In function 'unsafeSend' at line 58: always capture and check the return value of 'target.call'.
    (bool success, bytes memory data) = target.call;
    require(success, "Call failed");
If failure should not revert, at minimum emit an event so off-chain monitoring can detect silent failures.

In function 'proxyCall' at line 66: add a zero-address guard before delegatecall to 'success':
  require(success != address(0), "Implementation not set");
  (bool ok,) = success.delegatecall(data);
  require(ok, "Delegatecall failed");
An uninitialised implementation slot silently no-ops all calls.

Add an explicit balance check before the transfer:
  require(balances[msg.sender] >= amount, 'Insufficient balance');
  balances[msg.sender] -= amount;   // Update state first
  payable(msg.sender).transfer(amount);
